Package: nano-full
Submenu: Editors
Version: 6.2-0
Depends: +libc +USE_GLIBC:librt +USE_GLIBC:libpthread +libncurses
Conflicts: 
Menu-Depends: 
Provides: 
Build-Variant: full
Section: utils
Category: Utilities
Repository: base
Title: GNU nano text editor (all features, Unicode)
Maintainer: Hannu Nyman <hannu.nyman@iki.fi>
Source: nano-6.2.tar.xz
License: GPL-3.0-or-later
LicenseFiles: COPYING
Type: ipkg
Description:   nano-full - all features, including syntax highlighting (also uci),
  multibuffer, Unicode/UTF-8, nanorc, some key bindings.
  (libmagic-based file type detection is disabled)

  Example /etc/nanorc is included. nanorc documentation at
  https://www.nano-editor.org/dist/latest/nanorc.5.html

    Nano is a small and simple text editor for use on the terminal.

  Nano started as an enhanced clone of the Pico text editor.
  Nowadays Nano wants to be a generally useful editor with sensible
  defaults (linewise scrolling, no automatic line breaking).

  Nano is an official GNU package.
https://www.nano-editor.org/
Hannu Nyman <hannu.nyman@iki.fi>
